title: NYPD identify woman found dead in Queens park
text:
NEW YORK (AP) - The NYPD has identified the body of a woman found in a Queens park with slash wounds to her neck and stomach.
Police say 28-year-old Qing Qing Kiemde, of Queens, was discovered just before 3 p.m. Sunday inside Kissena Park in Flushing.
She was pronounced dead at the scene.
There have been no arrests.
